ources-for-developers.aspx">Doug=20
Mahugh</A> have compiled great lists of tips, resources, and pointers to =
Open=20
XML developer documentation. You should check out their blogs!</P>
<H3>Coming Soon - Open XML Format SDK: April CTP</H3>
<P>Just as we speak, the Office Developer Documentation group (aka MSDN =
Office=20
group) is busy building a new CTP for the Open XML Format SDK. <A=20
href=3D"http://blogs.msdn.com/erikaehrli/archive/2008/02/11/open-xml-at-t=
he-microsoft-office-developer-conference-2008.aspx"=20
target=3D_blank=20
mce_href=3D"http://blogs.msdn.com/erikaehrli/archive/2008/02/11/open-xml-=
at-the-microsoft-office-developer-conference-2008.aspx">While=20
I was at the Office Developer Conference this year</A>, many people =
asked about=20
the future of this SDK and wanted to know if we were to release a Go =
Live=20
license soon. <A=20
href=3D"http://blogs.msdn.com/dmahugh/archive/2008/03/13/open-xml-sdk-roa=
dmap.aspx"=20
target=3D_blank=20
mce_href=3D"http://blogs.msdn.com/dmahugh/archive/2008/03/13/open-xml-sdk=
-roadmap.aspx">The=20
answer is yes!</A> Based on customer feedback, the product team improved =
the=20
June CTP version of the Open XML API. This release also includes support =
for=20
cool C# 3.0 and VB.NET 9.0 features, <A=20
href=3D"http://blogs.msdn.com/ericwhite/archive/2008/03/14/technical-impr=
ovements-in-the-open-xml-sdk.aspx"=20
target=3D_blank=20
mce_href=3D"http://blogs.msdn.com/ericwhite/archive/2008/03/14/technical-=
improvements-in-the-open-xml-sdk.aspx">such=20
as LINQ Annotations</A>. Watch <A=20
href=3D"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Dt_FYHd234ng" target=3D_blank=20
mce_href=3D"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3Dt_FYHd234ng">Zeyad's and =
Eric's=20
interview</A> for more details.</P>
<P>So this month, not only we got the happy news that the <A=20
href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2008/apr08/04-01OpenXMLV=
otePR.mspx"=20
target=3D_blank=20
mce_href=3D"http://www.microsoft.com/presspass/press/2008/apr08/04-01Open=
XMLVotePR.mspx">Office=20
Open XML was approved as an ISO standard</A>, developers will also get a =
new=20
release of the Open XML Format SDK. As soon as we publish the new SDK, =
I'll be=20
blogging about what's new with the SDK and I'll be sharing more code =
samples so=20
you can play with this new release.</P>
<P>Last but not least, for those of you who are eager to get started =
with Open=20
XML, here's a cool video where Brian Jones shows <A=20
href=3D"http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb264572.aspx" =
target=3D_blank=20
mce_href=3D"http://msdn2.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb264572.aspx">how =
to build=20
Word 2007 document using the Office Open XML Formats</A>.</P><IFRAME=20
style=3D"WIDTH: 500px; HEIGHT: 375px"=20
src=3D"http://msbluelight-0.agappdom.net/e1/d/20709/586316/63344412000/0.=
vAszHDQpKqSqUGNGdECxZPjSjFo/zziframehtml1zz.html"=20
frameBorder=3D0 scrolling=3Dno=20
mce_src=3D"http://silverlight.services.live.com/invoke/61729/Word2007Offi=
ceOpenXML/iframe.html"></IFRAME>
<P>Happy times!</P>
